{"TopicId":192479,"ForumId":39,"TopicTitle":"My KSP Controller (SpaceX inspired)","CreatedByName":"Tabb","CreatedById":199087,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-17T20:44:35Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Tabb","CreatedById":199087,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-17T20:44:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en-us\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en-us\u0022\u003EHi all. I\u2019m quite proud to show you the controller I have been working on for the last few months. I started it last summer and I had to take a break for lack of time. But I eventually finished this.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en-us\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en-us\u0022\u003EFirst of all, I want to thank hugopeeter who helped me a lot! This is when I saw \u003Cb\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.instructables.com/id/KerbalController-a-Custom-Control-Panel-for-Rocket/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehis own KSP controller\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/b\u003E that I decided to build my own.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en-us\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en-us\u0022\u003EAs you can see, I took inspiration from SpaceX Crew Dragon v2 cockpit. I wanted my controller to have a clean look, like this:\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022spaxeX.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002266.67\u0022 height=\u0022424\u0022 width=\u0022636\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/R64pnj4/spaxeX.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en-us\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en-us\u0022\u003EI also wanted it to be backlighted so that texts and indicators are visible in the dark. This is another reason it took me so long. It was hard to find a company able to lasercut the parts, for a reasonable price. This is a French company (\u003Cb\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.idmarquage.com/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EID Marquage\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/b\u003E) who did this. And I must say this looks amazing. The faceplate let light through and there is a black layer on the back. This layer has been laser engraved where light needs to be visible (texts and indicators).\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en-us\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en-us\u0022\u003ESo here is the final result:\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022result1.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022480\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/6wGpv7k/result1.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022result2.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022480\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/HCLsmWL/result2.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022result3.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022480\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/VYmZJw1/result3.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022result4.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022480\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/9bt3805/result4.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0With all lights off:\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022off.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022480\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/8z4vFc8/off.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en-us\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en-us\u0022\u003EAnd some close up of different parts:\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en-us\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en-us\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E button leds indicate the current state, as for breaks and gears.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022throttle.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022480\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/8MF2mKW/throttle.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en-us\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en-us\u0022\u003EOne joystick controls rotation, the other, translation. This is great for maneuvers like docking where both are used.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022josticks.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022480\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/NZHcMKn/josticks.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en-us\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en-us\u0022\u003EAntenna and solar panels buttons are set up on actions 10 and 9, the Abort one on the Cancel group.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022actions.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022480\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/XjBdGrD/actions.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en-us\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en-us\u0022\u003EThe ledbars indicates ressources level. The LCD screen displays flight parameters depending on the selected mode with the surrounding buttons.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022level2.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022480\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/P9MsN6F/level2.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en-us\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en-us\u0022\u003EThe original quote from Chris Hardwick is \u201CNo human ever became interesting by not failing.\u201D\u003Cbr\u003E\nI found it very appropriate for Kerbals \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue2.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:sticktongue:\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022citation.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022480\u0022 width=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/RScc9Y8/citation.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnfortunately, I didn\u2019t do pictures while assembling it (shame on me \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:/\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon1.png\u0022 title=\u0022:/\u0022\u003E).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en-us\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en-us\u0022\u003EHere is a video of the controller in use (sorry for the poor quality, the camera didn\u2019t like the backlight):\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://youtu.be/Ux8fxc0-acM\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://youtu.be/Ux8fxc0-acM\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan lang=\u0022en-us\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en-us\u0022\u003EEdit : Here are the Inkscape files for the panel \u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1HdtE2tBRrK2WDYcT2DtAPfRQp1_Y5Sz2?usp=sharing\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1HdtE2tBRrK2WDYcT2DtAPfRQp1_Y5Sz2?usp=sharing\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit2 : Here is my code \u003Ca href=\u0022https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1wmlQa6WcZRmjfZkodxGgqR8sXTvQqBis?usp=sharing\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1wmlQa6WcZRmjfZkodxGgqR8sXTvQqBis?usp=sharing\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-06-01T09:58:25Z\u0022 title=\u002206/01/2020 09:58  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EJune 1, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Tabb\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"hugopeeters","CreatedById":183934,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-18T06:09:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLike I said on the Instructables website: fantastic result! I am honored to have inspired you to make this. And happy that you\u2019ve actually succeeded.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dafni","CreatedById":149636,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-18T06:32:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAmazing work man! Very impressive!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf ever you want to build another one for money, just name your price \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tabb","CreatedById":199087,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-18T08:13:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223758141\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192479\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221584513173\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022149636\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dafni\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Dafni said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAmazing work man! Very impressive!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf ever you want to build another one for money, just name your price \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you man !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t plan to do another at the moment. This is really a lot of work !\u003Cbr\u003E\nMaybe later \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dafni","CreatedById":149636,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-18T09:27:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223758158\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192479\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221584519220\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022199087\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tabb\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Tabb said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you man !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t plan to do another at the moment. This is really a lot of work !\u003Cbr\u003E\nMaybe later \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou are welcome. Work like this needs to be seen. Really a great job.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, I bet it was a lot of work. I see how this is a lot to ask. The offer stands though, I would make it worth your while. If ever you are in the mood just hit me up.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe only thing I would add to my dream setup would be buttons for switch to prev/next vessel (for the dockings and Falcon9 style booster landings) and buttons for the timewarp.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPersonally I play with a hack setup, two joysticks, peddals, a throttle lever and some xbox controllers velcro\u0027d to my desk. It\u0027s a lot of fun, so much better for KSP than just a keyboard... especially the dual sticks. The xbox controllers give me lots of buttons and axes too, for the camera and all that. But it looks very makeshift indeed, total hack job.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHave fun with your setup and fly some nice missions!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ncheers\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDaf\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerballingSmasher","CreatedById":195689,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-18T19:01:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow. that\u0027s cool.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Terzh","CreatedById":217278,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-04T20:13:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI am planning to make my own KSP controller and I really like your faceplate with the backlight so want to do something similar. I want to make sure it is sturdy enough so am not sure what thickness I should pick for the faceplate. Can you share what thickness of the acrylic you used?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Staticalliam7","CreatedById":216180,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-08T16:46:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBravo!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MrShartySprinkles","CreatedById":220516,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-28T07:16:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSeriously amazing product! How do you get more buttons than the originals version? And a huge thanks for the laser cutting files!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}